arm64: dts: h713: fix fan-power gpio-hog cell count (3-wire fan)

Bench bring-up of the cooling fan showed the fan never spins even though the
SoC PWM is provably working. Instrumentation on the fan header (a 3-wire fan:
Red +V, Black GND, Yellow tach) found the tach line sitting at its 3.3 V
pull-up -- so the board's fan-sense is wired and the header is meant to be
driven -- but the +V pin floating at ~1.1 V and decaying, i.e. no supply. The
fan is a plain on/off load; its speed is not PWM-controlled, and its power
rail was simply never enabled.

Root cause: the fan_power_hog that is supposed to hold PB5 (the shared
backlight/fan power enable) high is malformed. sunxi pio is a #gpio-cells=3
controller whose specifier is <bank pin flags>, but the hog used a single
linear GPIO number, gpios = <37 ...> (2 cells). gpiolib cannot parse that and
silently skips the hog, so PB5 was never driven and the fan +V stayed off.
/sys/kernel/debug/gpio confirmed gpiochip0 had zero claimed lines. Correct it
to the 3-cell form <1 5 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH> (bank B = 1, pin 5 = PB5). This also
restores the backlight-enable rail on the projector, which shares PB5 and the
same broken hog.

This supersedes the earlier pwm-fan-on-PWM0 approach staged for this fan. The
main-PWM channel 0 output on PH17 was verified live (debugfs reported the
channel enabled with a register read-back of 39958/40000 ns, and pinmux showed
PH17 muxed to pwm0), which validated the corrected patch-0007 register map on
real silicon -- but it does nothing to a 3-wire fan, whose PH17 line is the
tachometer input, not a control output. So the pwm-fan node, its &pwm pinctrl
override, and CONFIG_HWMON / CONFIG_SENSORS_PWM_FAN are dropped; with the hog
fixed the fan simply runs whenever powered, which is the intended minimal
always-on behavior. Tachometer read-back (PH17) is left as possible future
work and deliberately not modeled here.

--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-h713.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-h713.dtsi
@@ -485,10 +485,16 @@
 
 
 
-			/* PB5 = panel_bl_en AND fan power - must stay HIGH */
+			/*
+			 * PB5 = panel-backlight enable AND cooling-fan power; must stay
+			 * HIGH so the fan's +V rail is driven. sunxi gpio specifiers are
+			 * 3-cell <bank pin flags> (bank B = 1, pin 5); the earlier
+			 * <37 ...> was a linear number on a #gpio-cells=3 controller, so
+			 * gpiolib could not parse the hog and left the rail off.
+			 */
 			fan_power_hog: fan-power-hog {
 				gpio-hog;
-				gpios = <37 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;
+				gpios = <1 5 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;
 				output-high;
 				line-name = "pb5-bl-fan-power";
 			};
